Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Bring a #large saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp} for the ravioli.

Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{3} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Pop the @baby plum tomatoes{125%g} onto a #baking tray{}. Drizzle with oil, sprinkle over half the garlic, season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}, then toss to coat.

When the oven is hot, roast the tomatoes on the middle shelf until they've softened and started to burst, ~{12-15%minutes}.

Meanwhile, when boiling, add the @spinach and ricotta ravioli{250%g} to the water and bring back to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{3%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{}. Drizzle with oil and stir through to stop it sticking together.

Halve the @ciabatta{1} and lay onto a baking tray, cut-side up. Spread over the remaining garlic and drizzle over the @olive oil{1%tbsp} for the garlic bread.

Bake the garlic bread on the top shelf of your oven until golden, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Meanwhile, heat a large saucepan on medium heat (no oil).

Add the @vegetable stock paste{10%g}, @creme fraiche{150%g}, @fresh pesto{32%g} and @water{50%ml} for the sauce. Stir to combine and bring to the boil.

Simmer until thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Meanwhile, in a #medium bowl{}, add the @balsamic vinegar{12%ml}, @wild rocket{40%g} and a drizzle of olive oil. Season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}, then toss to combine.

Once the sauce has thickened, stir through half the @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g} until melted.

Add the cooked ravioli to the pan and gently toss to coat in the sauce, then remove from the heat.

Share the ultimate creamy pesto ravioli between your #serving bowls{}. Sprinkle over the remaining cheese.

Top with the roasted tomatoes and a handful of rocket. Finish with a sprinkle of the @toasted flaked almonds{15%g}.

Cut the garlic bread diagonally into triangles and serve alongside with the remaining salad.

Enjoy!